Description: Handle sherd of Chian Wild Goat Style pottery dinos; white slip; four-reeded vertical ring handle; interior reserved; exterior: glazed black above and to sides of handle; band above reserved area below; some bands across reeds, much worn.
Bibliographic references: Lemos 1991 / Archaic Pottery of Chios. The Decorated Styles (p. 246, no. 288)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.0009) (phase 2)
